&gt; This is not a fatal JVM defect. In fact, it looks like it isn&#39;t a JVM
&gt; defect, but bug in the Linux glibc/pthread libraries. It only affects
&gt; the results of System.exit, so it&#39;s not even a fatal bug for JUnit. The
&gt; *only* thing that doesn&#39;t work is the exit codes.
&gt;
&gt; Since the the two failures reported in:
&gt;
&gt; http://www.egroups.com/message/junit/257
&gt;
&gt; are identical to those in:
&gt;
&gt; http://www.egroups.com/message/junit/108
&gt;
&gt; I took the leap of assuming they are caused by the same underlying
&gt; problem. The bug was initially claimed to be in libc.so 2.2, but not in
&gt; 2.1.2 which is the default RedHat libc so I could be wrong. Later data
&gt; (January 10 of this year) suggests that libpthread-0.9 is the culprit.
&gt;
&gt; The JVM defect was discussed in:
&gt;
&gt; http://www.egroups.com/message/junit/113
&gt;
&gt; and is listed at Sun:
&gt;
&gt; http://developer.java.sun.com/developer/bugParade/bugs/4388732.html
&gt;
&gt; Regards,
